description.p:
According to particular embodiments:



    

the plate has an overall rectangular or isosceles trapezoid shape, drilled with holes crossed with means for fastening the plate to the pylon;

the fork joint of the plate axially crosses the rudder bar so that the end of the fork joint appears on the side of the transmission connecting rods with respect to the transversal axis of the rudder bar;

the fork joint of the plate has overall an isosceles trapezoid shape with a small base end beyond the rudder bar, between the two transmission connecting rods so that all the sides of the spars of the rudder bar extend along the male fork joint, the plate having a transversal bulk substantially similar to that of the rudder bar;

the plate and the fork joint overall have the shape of an isosceles trapezoid.
